  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Depressive episode according to DSM-5 criteria

          -  Unipolar depression

          -  MADRS ≥ 20

          -  Antidepressive treatment (Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors/Serotonin Norepinephrine
             Reuptake Inhibitors)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Other comorbid mental disorders (bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, recent addiction &lt; 3
             months except for tobacco)

          -  Depression with psychotic features

          -  Serious unstabilized somatic illness

          -  Protected persons

          -  Dementia suspected at the time of enrollment
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
